# Versona routing (Forge)

## Principles

- **Versonas** are discipline lenses (`versona-*.mdc`); **not** a substitute for team meetings. Sessions live under `forge-logs/versona/<actor>/<session-id>/`.
- Use **`versona-all`** (or packaged **`forge-versona`**) for **routing** when unsure which discipline to attach.
- **Product Spark ≠ Forge Spark** — routing and planning rules must keep release slices separate from executable tasks.

## When to route

| Situation | Suggested lens / rule |
|-----------|------------------------|
| Intake / classification | `request-classifier` + prompts; then discipline as needed |
| Meta scope / roadmap | `meta-request-decomposer`; **Product Management** family; **PM** for commitments |
| Daily execution | `spark-planner`, **`forge-daily`** (if installed), `forge/charge.md` |
| Quality / test §5 | **`versona-testing`** |
| Estimation method | **`versona-estimation`** (if installed) |
| Defects | `defect-rca-testing` + **Testing** / **SE** |
| Standards / compliance | **`resolve-versona-standards`** Skill; **Security** / **Compliance** when triggered |

## Install / sync

- Copy discipline templates from [`blueprints/sdlc/methodologies/forge/versona/catalog/`](../../../../methodologies/forge/versona/catalog/) or run [`blueprints/sdlc/methodologies/forge/setup/sync-forge-cursor-rules.sh`](../../../../methodologies/forge/setup/sync-forge-cursor-rules.sh) per [`CURSOR-RULES-QUICKSTART.md`](../../../../methodologies/forge/setup/CURSOR-RULES-QUICKSTART.md).
- Align **`forge/forge.config.yaml`** with installed rules.

